The thing that got me thinking about it, is wanting to do something other than kill monsters and tradeskills. Like, I wish there were games you could play in game. not /gems, but games you play with your characters, like hide and seek, chess with lifesize chess peices, tag, things like that. A zoo would be something fun to do, other than the usual grind.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Does anyone have any ideas for some in-game games that you and your friends could play during a guild event?  It may involve combat of a sort, but doesn't have to.<br>
<br>
I've always wanted to host a kind of football tournament in The Arena (zone).  You start with two teams, realtively equal in combat ability (levels, classes). A level 1 gnome stands in the center and consents four members of each team -- the team chooses who gets to have consent.  When the referee kills the gnome, the game begins.<br>
<br>
The object of the game is to drag the gnome corpse to the goals formed by the spires on opposite sides of the arena.  Of course, only those with consent can actually drag the corpse.  The rest of the players act as &quot;blockers&quot; for the offense or as &quot;defenders&quot; of the goal.<br>
<br>
Rules could vary but most everything would be fair game.  You can root or snare the draggers.  You can PvP any member of the opposing team, but may not kill your own team members or yourself.  Specific rules can be adjusted if the sides are not really balanced (only one bard, for example, might mean no bard speed songs).  Rezzing in game is optional.  Points are awarded for goals, but can also be awarded for kills.<br>
<br>
The game lasts until everyone on one side is dead or until the corpse poofs (30 minutes).  If your team is behind, you probably don't want to kill everyone on the other team, as that will end the game <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyone else have other ideas?<br>
